  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2022-03-17",
    "date": "2022-03-23T15:43:36Z",
    "text": "This bill expresses the sense of Congress that energy rebates to individual taxpayers are required due to the global disruptions caused by COVID-19 and the Russian invasion of Ukraine.\n\nThe bill allows an income-based tax credit beginning in 2022 for the sum of monthly energy rebates. The amount of such rebates in any calendar month is the sum of $100 ($200 for married couples filing jointly) plus $100 multiplied by the number of the taxpayer's dependents during 2022."
  },
